operators : these are used to perform various operations on variables

1) Arithmetic Operators :


int x = 10,y=6;

A) Addition   : to add any two variables; x+y = 16
B) Subtraction : to subtract two variables : x-y :4; 
C) Multiplication  :  x*y = 60;
D) Division : x/y = 1
E) Modulus : x%y=4
F) Increment : x++ // 11, y++ //7
G) Decrement : x--//9,y--//5


2) Assignment Operators : these are used to assign values to the variables

A) = : x=90;
B)+= : x+=10;  //{x=x+10}
C)-= :x-=10; //{x=x-10}
D)*= :x*=10 //{x=x*10}
E)%= : x%=10  //{x=x%10}


order of evaluation : right to left


3) Comparison Operators : these are used to compare the values among variables








		
		
		
	
right to left